<font color="#FF0000">THAT DEADLY THUMP</font><br>
<tt>Thu Oct 30 23:11:50 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Sounds,<br><br>
An explosion of any kind.  Even worse is the concussion.  Remember the thump when the over pressure would over take you?<br><br>
I can see the airplane on its wing throttles to the wall.  Hear the engines screaming.  Watch the wing start to fold as the aircraft struggles for air.  Watch the tip tank fold over and burst and then the sick feeling as she rolled over, but somehow continued 360 degrees.  The ejection seats begin to fire they are 400 ft in the air as the fireball from the ground races upward to meet them.  It is over.  They settle in to the inevitable.  The shock wave hits. An aircraft on final at full power struggling for altitude banks steep to the left on the edge of a stall and just touches the fireball and then recovers. You can hear voices in your head when no one else can.  My friend has said goodbye.  I am so desperate to do something and can't move.  An eternity took only a few seconds. You just sit and watch the fire burn and hear the sirens scream and hear the occasional thump as tanks continue to explode.<br><br>
Need to stop now.  Hate the sound of explosions to this day.
<p><code>-- Wobbly Now  (SW) </code><p>


